thread.title: Eels star Semi Radradra punched partner two weeks after birth, court told
thread.title_full: Eels star Semi Radradra punched partner two weeks after birth, court told

author: Melanie Kembrey
title: Eels star Semi Radradra punched partner two weeks after birth, court told
text:
NRL player Semi Radradra arrives at Parramatta court. Photo: Peter Rae 
Ms Ting told the court she had wanted her mother to travel from Fiji to be with her, but Radradra had not filled out the forms to help her get a visa. 
After her mother rang her on the phone, the court heard, Ms Ting and Radradra had an argument in the bedroom. Advertisement 
Radradra, the court heard, was upset about the length of the conversation. 
"I just grabbed the phone and smashed the phone on the wall ... I told him 'he's a liar'," Ms Ting said. 
"He stood up and he punched me." 
Ms Ting told the court she started crying and locked herself in the bathroom. She overheard Radradra call a pastor and ask him to come the home. 
Translating from Fijian, Ms Ting told the court that Radradra told the pastor: "I used my hands on her". 
The pastor, the court heard, talked to the pair together and they read a Bible verse before he left. 
Five witnesses are expected to give evidence at the hearing. Advertisement
